node.text: Please, call me Gus! Mr. Cannworthy is my father. | @drinkcann

node.text: A few months ago @beam sent me some of their CBD products to try out and I honestly really loved them. Their dream powder improved my sleep so much that I ended up investing in the company. Go buy Beam and help support @b_pups’ college fund. 😘

node.text: Back home in LA after a great week in Aspen for the @XGames. I'm incredibly grateful to the folks at @ESPN for putting on a COVID safe event when the pandemic has cancelled pretty much all of our other competitions so far this season. I didn't quite have the performance that I was hoping for but my body was a wreck and I'm proud of myself for battling through the injuries and putting down a run - even if it wasn't my best one ever. In awe of the level of skiing showcased this past weekend and feeling inspired and motivated to put my nose to the grindstone to step my run up for the next event (wherever/ whenever that may be). Big thanks to @monsterenergy @prada and @hoteljeromeaspen for taking such great care of me this weekend and to my coach @justin_dorey for all of the help and support!

node.text: Welcome to my home! There are no rules in this house. I'm not like a regular mom, I'm a cool mom! No, just kidding, put that fucking glass on a coaster or I'll rip your head off. Yes, I'm a nightmare BUT my apartment is a dream thanks to my friends @mrorlandosoria and @backup_design! I'm actually really passionate about interior design and from the beginning of this remodel I had strong opinions and a clear vision of what I wanted to do with the space but I wouldn't have been able to bring it to life without them. Thank you to @zekeruelas for shooting the beautiful pics and @derekblasberg for the kind words. Check out the full @archdigest article at the link in my bio! 🙏🏼❤️
